The paper discusses the use of attention-based neural networks for explaining the models learned from propositional data. This falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, specifically in the sub-field of interpretability and explainability of models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with natural language processing (NLP) models, which could place it in cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks for image classification, which could place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the use of feature interactions, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
